{
  "stem": "15197.5",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I was walking there, and the first I remember that I organized at that time, the first Jewish event of people-- of survivors for survivors.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I did it with all my soul, what I still had in me, and Jewish songs.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it is very characteristic that in the camps many Jewish songs were created.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "In the Vilna ghetto, many songs were created.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And at this event, they were singing-- those who had voices.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the reaction, the response of the people who came, was overwhelming.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Overwhelming.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "What?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, they were Jewish songs from the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In the Vilna ghetto for instance, I cannot sing here.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Maybe someday, but not now.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the Vilna ghetto, they had theater during deportation time.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In the Warsaw ghetto were Polish songs.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But people were singing.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And also, they were singing Israeli songs.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Because at that time, it was the trend and the feeling to go to Israel, to go to your own country, which is not your own yet.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was an atmosphere of survival and, at the same time, of sadness.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "A realization that you are-- after all, you survived, but you are alone.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And this was very difficult to live with.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "You went on-- you was constantly waiting, maybe, maybe, maybe, hoping and realizing, day by day, time passed, that no, this is the reality.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And at the same time, thinking that life goes on.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Life goes on.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And then, in Poland, it was, again, anti-Semitic incident.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "People coming from the forest, from two small towns, were robbed, were killed.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "The Poles, Ukrainians, and other, they didn't want them back.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
